---
layout: base
title: "Suggest a Playlist"
description: Know a YouTube playlist curated around freethought, humanism, or rationalist themes? Share it and we'll review it for inclusion in our background player.
permalink: /music/playlists/submit/
---

<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">
  <div class="container--prose">

    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="breadcrumbs__list">
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/projects/">Projects</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/music/">Freethought Music</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/music/playlists/">Playlists</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item breadcrumbs__item--current" aria-current="page">Suggest a Playlist</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Freethought Music</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-masthead); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3.815rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Suggest a playlist</h1>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-loose); max-width: 62ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
        We feature curated YouTube playlists grouped by mood, era, or theme. If you maintain one &mdash; or know of one &mdash; whose spirit fits freethought, tell us about it.
      </p>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-faint); max-width: 62ch;">
        Looking to suggest a single track instead? <a href="/music/submit/" style="color: var(--color-link);">Suggest a song &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
        <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--color-ink); padding-bottom: var(--space-2); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-ink);">What we're looking for</h2>
        <ul style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-base); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); padding-left: var(--space-5); margin-bottom: 0;">
          <li><strong>Curated, not algorithmic.</strong> A human hand picked the tracks. No autoplay mixes, no "Top Hits of 2019," no machine-generated radio stations.</li>
          <li><strong>On YouTube.</strong> YouTube Music and YouTube playlists both work &mdash; anything with a <code>playlist?list=&hellip;</code> URL. Spotify-only playlists can't embed on our site.</li>
          <li><strong>A clear through-line.</strong> A mood ("late-night reading"), an era ("Enlightenment-era classical"), or a theme ("songs about doubt") &mdash; something a reader can feel.</li>
          <li><strong>Public &amp; stable.</strong> Private or frequently-deleted playlists won't work &mdash; the tracks need to stay reachable.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8); padding: var(--space-5); background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);">
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-ink); margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);">Finding the playlist ID</h3>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">
          Open the playlist on YouTube or YouTube Music. Look at the URL bar for the <code>list=</code> parameter &mdash; everything after the equals sign (up to the next <code>&amp;</code>) is the playlist ID.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-faint); background: var(--color-bg); padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); overflow-x: auto; margin: 0;">
          https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=<strong style="color: var(--color-accent);">PLZzyUfYacyoJjeBe_unngyzRyczmzag5-</strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <form action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST" class="w3f" style="margin: var(--space-6) 0;">
        <input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="{{ site.forms.accessKey }}">
        <input type="hidden" name="subject" value="Playlist suggestion, {{ site.title }}">
        <input type="hidden" name="redirect" value="{{ site.url }}/thank-you/">
        <input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="{{ site.title }} Music Form">
        <input type="checkbox" name="botcheck" class="visually-hidden" style="display:none" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-url">Playlist URL <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="url" name="playlist_url" id="pl-url" required aria-required="true" placeholder="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=...">
          <p class="w3f__hint">The full URL from your browser's address bar, so we can verify it embeds correctly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-id">Playlist ID <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="playlist_id" id="pl-id" placeholder="PLZzyUfYacyoJjeBe_unngyzRyczmzag5-">
          <p class="w3f__hint">Just the ID after <code>list=</code>. If you're not sure, leave it blank &mdash; we'll extract it from the URL.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-name">Playlist name <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="name" id="pl-name" required aria-required="true" placeholder="Late-night reading mix">
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-category">Category <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <select class="w3f__input" name="category" id="pl-category" required aria-required="true">
            <option value="">Pick the best fit&hellip;</option>
            <option value="Focus">Focus &mdash; for concentrated reading or writing</option>
            <option value="Reflection">Reflection &mdash; slow, thoughtful, contemplative</option>
            <option value="Energy">Energy &mdash; for motivation and momentum</option>
            <option value="Protest">Protest &mdash; dissent, defiance, civil rights</option>
            <option value="Classical">Classical &mdash; orchestral, chamber, piano</option>
            <option value="Science">Science &mdash; wonder, cosmos, discovery</option>
            <option value="Ambient">Ambient &mdash; atmospheric background listening</option>
            <option value="Historical">Historical &mdash; from a specific era or tradition</option>
            <option value="Other">Other (describe below)</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-desc">Description <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <textarea class="w3f__textarea" name="description" id="pl-desc" rows="3" maxlength="500" required aria-required="true" placeholder="One line a reader would see. E.g.: 'Quiet piano pieces for late-night reading and deep thought.'"></textarea>
          <p class="w3f__hint">Keep it under 200 characters &mdash; this is what appears on the playlist card.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-why">Why this playlist fits freethought <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <textarea class="w3f__textarea" name="reason" id="pl-why" rows="4" maxlength="1200" required aria-required="true" placeholder="What's the through-line? Is it the artists, the lyrics, the mood, the historical context? A few sentences is plenty."></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-curator">Who curated it? <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="curator" id="pl-curator" placeholder="You? A YouTube creator? An organization?">
          <p class="w3f__hint">We credit curators when we can.</p>
        </div>

        <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule); margin: var(--space-6) 0;">

        <div class="w3f__row">
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-sname">Your name <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="submitter_name" id="pl-sname" autocomplete="name">
          </div>
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="pl-email">Email <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="email" name="email" id="pl-email" autocomplete="email" placeholder="only if you'd like a reply">
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="w3f__fineprint" style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-ink-faint); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); max-width: 62ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          We review every suggestion before adding it, and we may trim or re-order tracks for fit. We accept <em>curated</em> lists, not random aggregations. You'll only hear from us if we have a question.
        </p>

        <button type="submit" class="w3f__submit">Submit playlist</button>
      </form>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
